6:
Don't tell me the yokai spirited me
away to somewhere weird again...
10: Hm? Alk, did you hear something?
15:
No? But if there's noises coming
from near the Flipper... *sigh* Here
we go again.
19:
Oh! Pardon, could y'all tell me where
I am?
23:
Never seen trees like these 'round
my neck of the woods!
27:
This is Starview Village, an
observatory for distant worlds.
33:
Starview, huh? You DO have an
amazing view of the stars! Sweet 'n
simple—I like it!
39:
Uhh... Thanks? And who are you,
exactly?
44:
Oh, right! I'm Kohane! But y'all can
call me... Kohane!
48:
It's nice to meet you, Kohane. I am
Stella, and this is Alk.
53: Stella and Alk, gotcha. Cool, cool.
59:
Came to see what all the fuss was.
So, who'd the Flipper drag in this
time?
63:
AHA! So the yokai DID pull another
prank on me! You listen here,
furball—I ain't lettin' ya try anythin'
funny 'round these nice folks.
88:
STOP! They're not yokai! They're our
friends!
103:
That's me... Never lookin' before I
leap. I don't know how I can possibly
make it up to you.
106:
I guess... Fair's fair. I'll letcha both
take a free swing at me. Won't
dodge or nuthin'. Come at me!
111:
Ca-calm down, that's not
necessary. Nimbus and I are both
fine! See? No harm done!
116:
Whew, that's a relief! ...I really am
sorry, and thank ya both for bein' so
forgiving.
127:
I-I was all tensed up, but soon's I
relaxed, my legs noped out on me.
Man, I am STARVING.
129:
What I wouldn't do for some grub... If
I kick it, tell Master his... favorite
apprentice died... with honor...
138:
We were just on our way to get
lunch when we found you by the
World Flipper. You're welcome to join
us.
144: REALLY?! I'm in! Lead the way!
150:
MMMMMM! Thishviv—*gulp*—this is
the best meal I've ever had! What IS
this stuff?!
154:
While I'm glad you seem to have
perked up, it does make me a little
concerned. Kohane, how long has it
been since you last ate?
163:
Oh, you poor thing. No WONDER you
were starving to death.
166:
Right? See, Master sent me off for
my morning training before
breakfast, but on my way down the
mountain, I slipped 'n fell through
the clouds.
167:
Next I came to, I was stuck in that
tree y'all found me in. No breakfast,
and no money ta buy some.
170:
Wait, back up a second. Did you just
say you fell through the clouds?
175:
Yep! What, y'all never met a tengu
before?
178:
A tengu... Actually, I feel like I've
heard the word somewhere...
183:
Tengu are mountain-dwelling yokai
who live high in the peaks, above
the cloudline.
188:
Yokai, huh? They the, uh... friendly
kind? Y'know, I coulda sworn you
smelled human.
193:
Oh, yep. I'm human, but I was raised
by a tengu. Master found me
abandoned at the base of the
mountain and took me in!
198: S-sorry... We didn't mean to pry...
202:
Huh? Nahhh, don't go all gloomy on
me! I love Master, and I love livin' the
high life up in the mountains. I've got
a grizzly for a teddy bear!
208:
It is, but see... Lately, Master's been
tellin' me I need to get out and
experience human life.
209:
It's aaaalways, "Kohane! Young
ladies don't mud wrestle bears!"
Like... Speak for yourself, am I right?
213:
Ooh! While I'm down here in Pal...
Palepra? I might as give the city
slicker life a go! Yeah... Doesn't seem
like a bad place ta live!
218:
Where WILL you live, though? As I
recall, you mentioned you've no coin
to pay for lodging or board.
222:
Psssh. You think I'm gonna live in
one o' them giant dollhouses? Long
as I can find a nice tree to sleep in,
I'm good.
228:
Ah yes. Sleeping in trees. The
authentic city life experience.
231:
Kohane... How about you come and
live in Starview?
238:
Of course. Besides, something tells
me the Guild wouldn't take kindly to
a mysterious flying girl living in their
trees.
242:
We look forward to having you in
Starview.
248:
Awesome! That's me sorted, I guess.
Thank y'all so much!
252: Ooh, this is gonna be a blast!
